==English==
===Etymology===
Back formation from plural [[seraphim]], from Latin [[seraphim]], from Hebrew [[שרף]] (''saraf'') "fire".

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl=seraphs|pl2=seraphim}}

# (''Biblical'') A six winged [[angel]]; the highest [[choir]] or order of angels in Christian [[angelology]], ranked above [[cherubim]], and below [[God]].

